      "source": "https://hewlettharbor.gov/history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Auerbach Avenue takes its name from Joseph Auerbach, who purchased large parcels of land there in 1914.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hewlett_Harbor%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The 1860s arrival of the LIRR Far Rockaway Branch connected the area to rail, easing the shift from farms to estates.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
